<doc id="435512" wikidata="Q1772548" url="?curid=435512" title="Oberschule am Elsengrund">
<text>Oberschule am Elsengrund was a school in Mahlsdorf in Berlin, Germany. The school was founded in 1983 as a school for Polytechnique. After the reunification of Germany it became a comprehensive school. This school moved away in summer 1993 and in August of the same year it became a gymnasium (school) which is not existing anymore. It had about 750 students taught by around 50 teachers.

Foreign languages taught were English, French, Latin and Spanish.

==External links==

*Oberschule am Elsengrund (in German)</text><links>
